Ben Affleck appeared on PBS show Finding Your Roots about his family history . 
  He learned that one of his ancestors was a slave owner in New Jersey in the 1840s . 
  The actor asked producers to leave out the name of James McGuire from the show . 
  McGuire kept eight slaves on his farm in Trenton . 
  Affleck apologized on Facebook and said he was 'embarrassed' He said he lobbied for the information to be withheld after filming the episode . 
  PBS is now investigating the request . 
 